</div>
<div class="selected"></p>
<p><strong><em><a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Family-Upstairs-Lisa-Jewell/dp/1780899203/?tag=prhmarketing10454-21" rel="noopener" target="_blank">The Family Upstairs</a></em> by Lisa Jewell</strong><br />
<em>8 August</em><br />
This tense mystery has all the hallmarks of a great Lisa Jewell thriller: it&#8217;s dark, twisty and perfectly paced, with intriguing characters and a creepy premise. From the moment you open it, we promise you&#8217;ll struggle to put this book down &#8211; so cancel your plans, settle back and prepare to be gripped. <a href="https://www.deadgoodbooks.co.uk/extract-the-family-upstairs-by-lisa-jewell/">Read a chapter here.</a></p>
<p><strong><em><a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Turn-Key-Ruth-Ware/dp/1787300439/?tag=prhmarketing10454-21" rel="noopener" target="_blank">The Turn of the Key</a></em> by Ruth Ware</strong><br />
<em>8 August</em><br />
Full of menace, <em><a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Turn-Key-Ruth-Ware/dp/1787300439/?tag=prhmarketing10454-21" rel="noopener" target="_blank">The Turn of the Key</a></em> is a modern-day haunted house thriller from the author of <em><a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Dark-Wood-Ruth-Ware/dp/0099598248/?tag=prhmarketing10454-21" rel="noopener" target="_blank">In A Dark, Dark Wood</a></em> and <em><a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Death-Mrs-Westaway-Ruth-Ware/dp/1784704369/?tag=prhmarketing10454-21" rel="noopener" target="_blank">The Death of Mrs Westaway</a></em>. It&#8217;s a genuinely suspenseful read permeated with a creeping sense of dread, and it&#8217;s sure to have you holding your breath right up to the dramatic conclusion. <a href="https://www.deadgoodbooks.co.uk/extract-the-turn-of-the-key-by-ruth-ware/">Read a chapter here.</a></p>
<p><strong><em><a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Then-She-Vanishes-gripping-psychological/dp/1405932570/?tag=prhmarketing10454-21" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Then She Vanishes</a></em> by Claire Douglas</strong><br />
<em>8 August</em><br />
When her childhood best friend is accused of a terrible crime, Jess returns to the seaside town where they grew up to try and work out what happened. Full of twists and turns, this thrilling page turner is one you should bump up to the top of your reading list. <a href="https://www.deadgoodbooks.co.uk/claire-douglas-fairground-books/">Find out more about the book&#8217;s setting here.</a></p>
<p></div>
